gomodel:SYNGO_4725  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Figure 4: Confocal imaging of hippocampal neuronal cultures with co-staining for Homer1c-mCherry and EPS15-GFP show this protein is localized at the postsynapse. Instead of GFP tagging, endogenous EPS15 was also tagged using CRISPR/Cas-9.\n\nFigure 5: time-lapse experiments on neurons co-expressing Homer1c and fluorophore-tagged EPS15 showed high association with PSDs.\n\nFigure 6: to dissect the spatial organization of endocytic proteins relative to the clathrin structure at\nthe endocytic zone (EZ), authors used two-color single-molecule localization microscopy (SMLM). Halo-CLCa co-transfected with GFP-tagged EPS15 showed that it was often distributed in smaller patches around and sometimes within the EZ marked by CLCa.. Experimental description: M&M: \"Hippocampal cultures were prepared from brain of embryonic day 18 (E18) Wistar rats (both genders) as described before (Scheefhals et al., 2019)\"\n\n\"The knock-in constructs for GFP-Eps15, GFP-Itsn1 and GFP-Dyn2 were designed and cloned as described previously (Willems et al., 2020)\"\n\nGFP-Eps15 was a gift from Dr. Van Bergen en Henegouwen." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4973-5732" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" ;
        dc:date           "2022-07-31" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_4725" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

